sentences: Williams grew up in Arlington, Massachusetts.
After getting involved in the DIY scene in Boston as a teenager, Williams moved to Iowa.
In 2016, Williams released her second EP titled Contact Sports on a St. Louis-based DIY tape label called It Takes Time.
Williams' debut album, I Was Born Swimming, was released in 2020 via Polyvinyl Records.

This anticipated label debut earned overwhelming praise from the likes of Gorilla vs. Bear, NPR Music, and Paste, and she was named Rolling Stone Artist You Need To Know, Stereogum's Artist to Watch, The FADER's Gen F, and The Guardian's One to Watch.
